The paper focuses on the ergodic downlink sum-rate performance of a system consisting of a set of heterogeneous users, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also studies user selection schemes and beamforming methods, which are relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper presents numerical results, which could fall under machine learning (cs.MM) or machine learning (cs.LG) depending on the specific methods used.
